            Like all tools on ToolzTotal, this calculator operates completely client-side in your local browser sandbox. No details about your weight, height, age, or calculations are ever uploaded, sent to a server, or shared. No account signup is required.
          </div>
        </details>
      
        <details class="bg-canvas ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lvl2 group">
          <summary class="px-6 py-4 cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between font-sans font-semibold text-sm text-ink list-none hover:bg-canvas-soft transition-colors select-none">
            Why do bodybuilders often have an 'obese' BMI?
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-mute shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-sm text-body font-sans leading-relaxed border-t border-hairline pt-4">
            BMI is calculated using only weight and height, without taking body composition into account. Because muscle is denser and heavier than fat, bodybuilders carry extra weight in the form of muscle, causing their BMI score to fall into the overweight or obese category despite having low body fat.
          </div>
        </details>
      
        <details class="bg-canvas ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lvl2 group">
          <summary class="px-6 py-4 cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between font-sans font-semibold text-sm text-ink list-none hover:bg-canvas-soft transition-colors select-none">
            What is the Waist-to-Height Ratio (WHtR) and how is it used?
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-mute shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-sm text-body font-sans leading-relaxed border-t border-hairline pt-4">
            The Waist-to-Height Ratio (WHtR) is a health metric calculated by dividing your waist circumference by your height. A ratio of 0.50 or less is considered healthy, as it indicates that your waist circumference is less than half your height, which correlates with low abdominal and visceral fat levels.
          </div>
        </details>
      
        <details class="bg-canvas ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lvl2 group">
          <summary class="px-6 py-4 cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between font-sans font-semibold text-sm text-ink list-none hover:bg-canvas-soft transition-colors select-none">
            Is BMI accurate for senior citizens or older adults?
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-mute shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-sm text-body font-sans leading-relaxed border-t border-hairline pt-4">
            BMI can be less accurate for older adults due to age-related muscle loss (sarcopenia) and bone density loss. A senior citizen may have a 'normal' BMI but carry a high proportion of fat relative to muscle, meaning a slightly higher BMI (25-27) is often associated with better health outcomes in older populations.
          </div>
        </details>
      
        <details class="bg-canvas ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lvl2 group">
          <summary class="px-6 py-4 cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between font-sans font-semibold text-sm text-ink list-none hover:bg-canvas-soft transition-colors select-none">
            What is visceral fat and why does it matter?
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-mute shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-sm text-body font-sans leading-relaxed border-t border-hairline pt-4">
            Visceral fat is body fat that is stored inside the abdominal cavity, surrounding internal organs like the liver and pancreas. Unlike subcutaneous fat under the skin, visceral fat is metabolically active and releases inflammatory markers that increase the risk of heart disease, diabetes, and stroke.
          </div>
        </details>
      
        <details class="bg-canvas ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lvl2 group">
          <summary class="px-6 py-4 cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between font-sans font-semibold text-sm text-ink list-none hover:bg-canvas-soft transition-colors select-none">
            Can BMI be used to diagnose health issues?
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-mute shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-sm text-body font-sans leading-relaxed border-t border-hairline pt-4">
            No, BMI is a screening tool, not a diagnostic instrument. A high or low BMI indicates a potential risk category, but a healthcare provider must perform additional tests—such as measuring blood pressure, assessing diet, evaluating physical activity, and conducting blood tests—to diagnose a person's actual health status.
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Related Tools Section -->
    <section class="max-w-4xl pt-16 mt-20 border-t border-hairline" aria-label="Related Tools">
      <h3 class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-wider text-mute mb-8">Related Health Calculators</h3>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <a href="/health/calorie-calculator" class="group bg-canvas ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline hover:border-hairline-strong rounded-xl p-5 shadow-lvl1 hover:shadow-lvl2 transition-all">
          <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-ink font-sans group-hover:text-primary transition-colors flex items-center gap-2">
            Calorie Calculator
            <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-mute group-hover:text-primary group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-all" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
          </h4>
          <p class="text-mute text-xs font-sans mt-1.5">Estimate total daily energy expenditure and BMR.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/health/macro-calculator" class="group bg-canvas ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline hover:border-hairline-strong rounded-xl p-5 shadow-lvl1 hover:shadow-lvl2 transition-all">
          <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-ink font-sans group-hover:text-primary transition-colors flex items-center gap-2">
            Macro Calculator
            <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-mute group-hover:text-primary group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-all" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
          </h4>
          <p class="text-mute text-xs font-sans mt-1.5">Compute custom protein, carb, and fat distributions.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/health/body-fat-calculator" class="group bg-canvas ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline hover:border-hairline-strong rounded-xl p-5 shadow-lvl1 hover:shadow-lvl2 transition-all">
          <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-ink font-sans group-hover:text-primary transition-colors flex items-center gap-2">
            Body Fat Calculator
            <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-mute group-hover:text-primary group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-all" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
          </h4>
          <p class="text-mute text-xs font-sans mt-1.5">Estimate body fat using the US Navy method.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</Layout>

<script>
  // ============================================================
  // DOM Elements
  // ============================================================
  const btnMetric = document.getElementById('btn-metric') as HTMLButtonElement;
  const btnImperial = document.getElementById('btn-imperial') as HTMLButtonElement;

  const weightInput = document.getElementById('weight') as HTMLInputElement;
  const heightInput = document.getElementById('height') as HTMLInputElement;
  
  const lblWeight = document.getElementById('lbl-weight') as HTMLLabelElement;
  const lblHeight = document.getElementById('lbl-height') as HTMLLabelElement;

  const resBmi = document.getElementById('res-bmi') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const resClassBadge = document.getElementById('res-class-badge') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const resBmiPrime = document.getElementById('res-bmi-prime') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const resPonderal = document.getElementById('res-ponderal') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const resHealthyRange = document.getElementById('res-healthy-range') as HTMLSpanElement;

  const scalePointer = document.getElementById('scale-pointer') as HTMLDivElement;
  const pointerVal = document.getElementById('pointer-val') as HTMLSpanElement;

  // ============================================================
  // State
  // ============================================================
  let unitSystem: 'metric' | 'imperial' = 'metric';

  // ============================================================
  // Functions
  // ============================================================
  const updateUnitToggle = () => {
    if (unitSystem === 'metric') {
      btnMetric.classList.add('bg-canvas-soft-2', 'text-ink', 'font-semibold', 'border-hairline-strong');
      btnMetric.classList.remove('bg-canvas', 'text-body');
      btnImperial.classList.remove('bg-canvas-soft-2', 'text-ink', 'font-semibold', 'border-hairline-strong');
      btnImperial.classList.add('bg-canvas', 'text-body');
      lblWeight.textContent = "Weight (kg)";
      lblHeight.textContent = "Height (cm)";
      
      const w = parseFloat(weightInput.value);
      const h = parseFloat(heightInput.value);
      if (w) weightInput.value = Math.round(w / 2.20462).toString();
      if (h) heightInput.value = Math.round(h * 2.54).toString();
    } else {
      btnImperial.classList.add('bg-canvas-soft-2', 'text-ink', 'font-semibold', 'border-hairline-strong');
      btnImperial.classList.remove('bg-canvas', 'text-body');
      btnMetric.classList.remove('bg-canvas-soft-2', 'text-ink', 'font-semibold', 'border-hairline-strong');
      btnMetric.classList.add('bg-canvas', 'text-body');
      lblWeight.textContent = "Weight (lbs)";
      lblHeight.textContent = "Height (in)";
      
      const w = parseFloat(weightInput.value);
      const h = parseFloat(heightInput.value);
      if (w) weightInput.value = Math.round(w * 2.20462).toString();
      if (h) heightInput.value = Math.round(h / 2.54).toString();
    }
    calculate();
  };

  const calculate = () => {
    let weight = parseFloat(weightInput.value);
    let height = parseFloat(heightInput.value);

    if (isNaN(weight) || isNaN(height) || weight <= 0 || height <= 0) {
      return;
    }

    // Convert to metric internally
    let weightKg = weight;
    let heightCm = height;
    if (unitSystem === 'imperial') {
      weightKg = weight / 2.20462;
      heightCm = height * 2.54;
    }

    const heightM = heightCm / 100;

    // Calculations
    const bmi = weightKg / (heightM * heightM);
    const bmiPrime = bmi / 25;
    const ponderalIndex = weightKg / (heightM * heightM * heightM);

    // Dynamic Healthy weight range (BMI 18.5 to 24.9)
    const minHealthyWeight = 18.5 * (heightM * heightM);
    const maxHealthyWeight = 24.9 * (heightM * heightM);

    // Format outputs
    resBmi.textContent = bmi.toFixed(1);
    resBmiPrime.textContent = bmiPrime.toFixed(2);
    resPonderal.textContent = `${ponderalIndex.toFixed(1)} kg/m³`;

    if (unitSystem === 'metric') {
      resHealthyRange.textContent = `${minHealthyWeight.toFixed(1)} - ${maxHealthyWeight.toFixed(1)} kg`;
    } else {
      resHealthyRange.textContent = `${Math.round(minHealthyWeight * 2.20462)} - ${Math.round(maxHealthyWeight * 2.20462)} lbs`;
    }

    // Set Weight Classification
    let classLabel = "Normal Weight";
    let colorClass = "text-emerald-500";
    let borderClass = "border-emerald-500/20";
    let bgClass = "bg-emerald-500/10";

    if (bmi < 16) {
      classLabel = "Severe Thinness";
      colorClass = "text-blue-500";
      borderClass = "border-blue-500/20";
      bgClass = "bg-blue-500/10";
    } else if (bmi >= 16 && bmi < 17) {
      classLabel = "Moderate Thinness";
      colorClass = "text-blue-400";
      borderClass = "border-blue-400/20";
      bgClass = "bg-blue-400/10";
    } else if (bmi >= 17 && bmi < 18.5) {
      classLabel = "Mild Thinness";
      colorClass = "text-blue-300";
      borderClass = "border-blue-300/20";
      bgClass = "bg-blue-300/10";
    } else if (bmi >= 18.5 && bmi < 25) {
      classLabel = "Normal Weight";
      colorClass = "text-emerald-500";
      borderClass = "border-emerald-500/20";
      bgClass = "bg-emerald-500/10";
    } else if (bmi >= 25 && bmi < 30) {
      classLabel = "Overweight";
      colorClass = "text-yellow-500";
      borderClass = "border-yellow-500/20";
      bgClass = "bg-yellow-500/10";
    } else if (bmi >= 30 && bmi < 35) {
      classLabel = "Obesity Class I";
      colorClass = "text-orange-500";
      borderClass = "border-orange-500/20";
      bgClass = "bg-orange-500/10";
    } else if (bmi >= 35 && bmi < 40) {
      classLabel = "Obesity Class II";
      colorClass = "text-red-400";
      borderClass = "border-red-400/20";
      bgClass = "bg-red-400/10";
    } else {
      classLabel = "Obesity Class III";
      colorClass = "text-red-700 dark:text-red-400";
      borderClass = "border-red-700/20 dark:border-red-400/20";
      bgClass = "bg-red-700/10 dark:bg-red-400/10";
    }

    resClassBadge.className = `mt-4 px-2.5 py-1 text-xs font-semibold rounded-full w-fit ${bgClass} ${colorClass} ${borderClass} border`;
    resClassBadge.textContent = classLabel;

    // Pointer placement logic (Min display: 15, Max: 40+)
    let pct = ((bmi - 15) / (40 - 15)) * 100;
    if (pct < 0) pct = 0;
    if (pct > 100) pct = 100;

    scalePointer.style.left = `${pct}%`;
    pointerVal.textContent = bmi.toFixed(1);
  };

  // ============================================================
  // Event Listeners
  // ============================================================
  btnMetric.addEventListener('click', () => {
    if (unitSystem !== 'metric') {
      unitSystem = 'metric';
      updateUnitToggle();
    }
  });

  btnImperial.addEventListener('click', () => {
    if (unitSystem !== 'imperial') {
      unitSystem = 'imperial';
      updateUnitToggle();
    }
  });

  weightInput.addEventListener('input', calculate);
  heightInput.addEventListener('input', calculate);

  // Initial calculation
  calculate();
</script>
